<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The default arguments for Zend_Db_Select::join specify a wildcard for the "columns" argument. The integrity check of  Zend_Db_Table_Select, however, rejects queries which don't have an empty array for the columns value of joined tables. This means that something like:</p>

<p>$select = $myTable-&gt;select()-&gt;join('other_table', 'other_table.fk = my_table.id');</p>

<p>produces a select query that fails the integrity check. This is counter-intuitive; it would be helpful if Zend_Db_Table_Select added its own version of the join methods, which specified an empty array as the default argument for $columns.</p>

    </div>
